#: ../../../contributing/code/maintenance.rst:2
msgid "Maintenance"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/code/maintenance.rst:4
msgid ""
"During the lifetime of a minor version, new releases (patch versions) are"
" published on a monthly basis. This document describes the boundaries of "
"acceptable changes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/code/maintenance.rst:8
msgid "**Bug fixes** are accepted under the following conditions:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/code/maintenance.rst:10
msgid "The change does not break valid unit tests;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/code/maintenance.rst:11
msgid "New unit tests cover the bug fix;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/code/maintenance.rst:12
msgid "The current buggy behavior is not widely used as a \"feature\"."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/code/maintenance.rst:16
msgid ""
"When documentation (or PHPDoc) is not in sync with the code, code "
"behavior should always be considered as being the correct one."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/code/maintenance.rst:19
msgid "Besides bug fixes, other minor changes can be accepted in a patch version:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/code/maintenance.rst:21
msgid ""
"**Performance improvement**: Performance improvement should only be "
"accepted if the changes are local (located in one class) and only for "
"algorithmic issues (any such patches must come with numbers that show a "
"significant improvement on real-world code);"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/code/maintenance.rst:26
msgid ""
"**Newer versions of PHP**: Fixes that add support for newer versions of "
"PHP are acceptable if they don't break the unit test suite;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/code/maintenance.rst:29
msgid ""
"**Newer versions of popular OSes**: Fixes that add support for newer "
"versions of popular OSes (Linux, MacOS and Windows) are acceptable if "
"they don't break the unit test suite;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/code/maintenance.rst:33
msgid "**Translations**: Translation updates and additions are accepted;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/code/maintenance.rst:35
msgid ""
"**External data**: Updates for external data included in Symfony can be "
"updated (like ICU for instance);"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/code/maintenance.rst:38
msgid ""
"**Version updates for Composer dependencies**: Changing the minimal "
"version of a dependency is possible, bumping to a major one or increasing"
" PHP minimal version is not;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/code/maintenance.rst:42
msgid ""
"**Coding standard and refactoring**: Coding standard fixes or code "
"refactoring are not recommended but can be accepted for consistency with "
"the existing code base, if they are not too invasive, and if merging them"
" on master would not lead to complex branch merging;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/code/maintenance.rst:47
msgid "**Tests**: Tests that increase the code coverage can be added."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/code/maintenance.rst:49
msgid ""
"Anything not explicitly listed above should be done on the next minor or "
"major version instead (aka the *master* branch). For instance, the "
"following changes are never accepted in a patch version:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/code/maintenance.rst:53
msgid "**New features**;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/code/maintenance.rst:55
msgid ""
"**Backward compatibility breaks**: Note that backward compatibility "
"breaks can be done when fixing a security issue if it would not be "
"possible to fix it otherwise;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/code/maintenance.rst:59
msgid ""
"**Support for external platforms**: Adding support for new platforms "
"(like Google App Engine) cannot be done in patch versions;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/code/maintenance.rst:62
msgid ""
"**Exception messages**: Exception messages must not be changed as some "
"automated systems might rely on them (even if this is not recommended);"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/code/maintenance.rst:65
msgid "**Adding new Composer dependencies**;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/code/maintenance.rst:67
msgid ""
"**Support for newer major versions of Composer dependencies**: Taking "
"into account support for newer versions of an existing dependency is not "
"acceptable."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/code/maintenance.rst:71
msgid ""
"**Web design**: Changing the web design of built-in pages like "
"exceptions, the toolbar or the profiler is not allowed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/code/maintenance.rst:76
msgid ""
"This policy is designed to enable a continuous upgrade path that allows "
"one to move forward with newest Symfony versions in the safest way. One "
"should be able to move PHP versions, OS or Symfony versions almost "
"independently. That's the reason why supporting the latest PHP versions "
"or OS features is considered as bug fixes."
msgstr ""

